Classify the student's message. Return ONLY valid JSON, no other text.

{
  "intent": one of ["learn", "answer", "greeting", "off_topic"],
  "subject": subject name or null,
  "grade": integer or null,
  "topic": topic code or null,
  "kc_code": knowledge component code or null
}

Intent definitions:
- "learn": student wants to learn, practice, get an explanation, or is choosing a topic
- "answer": student is answering a question the tutor asked (a number, working, a value, an attempt at a solution)
- "greeting": hi, hello, thanks, bye
- "off_topic": anything not related to studying

KEY RULE: If the student's message looks like a short reply, a number, or working/calculations, it is almost always "answer".

TOOL USE:
When intent is "learn", you MUST call get_topics then get_topic to find the topic. Set "topic" and "kc_code" from the tool results.
If get_topic returns an error or "Topic not found", the topic is NOT in the curriculum. Set "topic" and "kc_code" to null. Do NOT guess or reuse a previous topic.

